BEGIN g-bbD189
CHAIN IF~Global("g-FWAMBUSH","GLOBAL",1) ~THEN g-bbD189 g-bbD189.chain1
@1 /*As you travel alongside Ulfbrand and his forces toward a towering corridor behind the high walls of the Great Foundry, you cannot help but wonder about two things. First, just how large a force did the Fated Factor manage to assemble on such short notice? You can only hope the Doomguard are prepared at the site of their ambush. The other thing that keeps drawing your attention is the notion of... consequence.. */
=@2 /*Your choices put this in motion. Could the Doomguard have hidden away? Could Ulfbrand have gotten distracted? Could Rowan Darkwood have changed his mind about this? Could Haer'Dalis and his troop have sneaked out of the City of Doors unseen, to some quaint Prime Material world to have more adventures of their own? All of these peaceful options are now off the table. This is going to get violent, and you helped it reach this point. */
=@3 /*How does it make you feel? */
END
IF~Global("g-actualcannibal","GLOBAL",1) !Global("g-kiaransaleefollower","GLOBAL",1)~THEN REPLY @5 /*Very good. The carnage will be wonderful. */ DO~IncrementGlobal("LAW","GLOBAL",-1) IncrementGlobal("GOOD","GLOBAL",-1) ActionOverride(Protagonist,PlaySong(%G-Factions1%))~ + g-bbD189.chain2
IF~Global("g-kiaransaleefollower","GLOBAL",1) !Global("Join_Dustmen","GLOBAL",1)~THEN REPLY @6 /*Very good. Utter a silent prayer to your new patron, the Lady of the Dead. The loss of life that is about to unravel is no cause for tears. The many bodies will likely be reused in their silent and perfect obedience of undead servitude. It is the ultimate goal of all life. */ DO~IncrementGlobal("LAW","GLOBAL",-1) IncrementGlobal("GOOD","GLOBAL",-2) IncrementGlobal("g-kiaransaleeworship","GLOBAL",5000) ActionOverride(Protagonist,PlaySong(%G-Factions1%))~ + g-bbD189.chain2
IF~Global("g-kiaransaleefollower","GLOBAL",1) Global("Join_Dustmen","GLOBAL",1)~THEN REPLY @7 /*Very good. Utter a silent prayer to your new patron, the Lady of the Dead. The loss of life that is about to unravel is no cause for tears. The many bodies will likely be reused in their silent and perfect obedience of undead servitude. It is the ultimate goal of all life. The philosophy of the Dustmen, so close to your heart, is so clearly in line with what the multiverse is heading towards. */ DO~IncrementGlobal("LAW","GLOBAL",-1) IncrementGlobal("GOOD","GLOBAL",-2) IncrementGlobal("g-kiaransaleeworship","GLOBAL",7000) ActionOverride(Protagonist,PlaySong(%G-Factions1%))~ + g-bbD189.chain2
IF~~THEN REPLY @8 /*Good. Only the strong will survive. This is the way of the planes. There is no reason to feel regret about it. */ DO~IncrementGlobal("LAW","GLOBAL",1) IncrementGlobal("GOOD","GLOBAL",-1) ActionOverride(Protagonist,PlaySong(%G-Factions1%))~ + g-bbD189.chain2
IF~~THEN REPLY @9 /*Good. The city will bathe in blood this day. The Fated want to take everyone's belongings. The Doomguard embrace decay and destruction. Neither are worth your tears. */ DO~IncrementGlobal("LAW","GLOBAL",-1) IncrementGlobal("GOOD","GLOBAL",-1) ActionOverride(Protagonist,PlaySong(%G-Factions1%))~ + g-bbD189.chain2
IF~~THEN REPLY @10 /*You do not know. You can only hope that this was the right path to take. */ DO~ActionOverride(Protagonist,PlaySong(%G-Factions1%))~ + g-bbD189.chain2
IF~~THEN REPLY @11 /*You are unsure. You have to believe that your choices are right. If this path is the only way to stop the slow undoing of the planes, it must be the right one, even if it seems terrible. */ DO~IncrementGlobal("LAW","GLOBAL",-1) ActionOverride(Protagonist,PlaySong(%G-Factions1%))~ + g-bbD189.chain2
IF~~THEN REPLY @12 /*Bad. Whatever secrets about your past await you in the deepest reaches of the Hells, they cannot be worth all the lives that will be lost today. Still, it is too late to stop this conflict. */ DO~IncrementGlobal("GOOD","GLOBAL",1) ActionOverride(Protagonist,PlaySong(%G-Factions1%))~ + g-bbD189.chain2
IF~~THEN REPLY @13 /*It does not make you feel anything. */ DO~ActionOverride(Protagonist,PlaySong(%G-Factions1%)) ~ + g-bbD189.chain2
CHAIN IF~~THEN g-bbD189 g-bbD189.chain2
@15 /*As the large squadron makes its way foundrywards, many locals hide indoors, shops close, and windows shutter to snuff the line of sight of curious children. Meanwhile, some creatures in the city have the opposite reaction. Many fiends stay outside and smile, sensing inevitable carnage. The legion of the Fated is made up of many men and women from Sigil, but also a significant number of seasoned warriors loyal to Ulfbrand, who traveled here from Ysgard. These streets rarely see such a display of power. */
=@16 /*There is a moment of tension as a patrol of Mercykillers appears, escorting a strange, amorphous creature, with an apparent victim still visible inside of it, partially digested. There are six of them, a force intimidating enough to scare most into submission, but their authority dwindles in the face of the continuous stream of silent, motivated creatures. They share some discreet whispers, perhaps discussing if it is even worth trying to do anything about this... */
END
IF~~THEN REPLY @18 /*Ignore all this. Focus on the task at hand. You are here to lead Ulfbrand into a trap. Do not stray from the path now. */ DO~CreateCreatureObject("g-bb156","g-bb155",0,0,0) SetGlobal("G-theaterabandoned","GLOBAL",1)~ + g-bbD189.chain3
