==DMorte IF~Global("G-AmbushmorteLoc3","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @470 /*"HEY! YOU BUNCH OF LEATHERHEADS! YOU CALL THAT SINGING? MY MOTHER WAS A THIGH BONE AND HAD NO VOCAL CHORDS, AND SHE SANG BETTER WHEN SOMEONE USED HER TO SMACK RICH BERKS ON THE HEAD!" */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushgraceLoc3","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @471 /*Fall-from-Grace sits crouched beside the wounded, casting her healing spells on them. Arrows and crackling bolts of magical energy whiz past just above her head, but she is clearly guided by a sense of duty that transcends concern for such details. */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushignusLoc3","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @472 /*Flames rain down from above on the members of the Fated, while Ignus's laughter echoes from the flank. */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushnordomLoc3","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @473 /*The rogue modron uses his elevated position to accurately fire bolts into the heads of the Fated fighting on the battlefield. The expression on his peculiar face betrays no strong emotions, perhaps only a hint of confusion. */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushdakkonLoc5","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @474 /*Dak'kon proves himself as an improvised second-line leader. Under his command, the offensive gains momentum, and the support line operates with greater confidence, feeling his protection. The githzerai himself also seems content with the role assigned to him. */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushvhailorLoc5","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @475 /*Vhailor mercilessly cuts down anyone who approaches the support line. His glowing eyes and blood-spattered armor make individual units less eager to try to break through toward the actors. */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushmorteLoc5","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @476 /*Morte is always where he is needed, darting swiftly between the flanks and the center of the line. Occasionally, his voice breaks through the singing as he hurls a resounding curse at Ulfbrand. */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushignusLoc5","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @477 /*Flames pour from Ignus's hands, engulfing both friends and foes alike. The Doomguard themselves seem to be screaming for him to stop. In a moment, they may try to take action. Nevertheless, the devastation among the Ysgardians is also quite substantial. */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushgraceLoc5","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @478 /*Grace moves through the second line, blessing and healing the archers and mages. She tends to stay behind them, which offers her some protection. Everyone accepts her help with gratitude. She is certainly a ray of hope for them in this terrifying battle. */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushnordomLoc5","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @479 /*Nordom climbs onto the sandbags. From there, he unleashes a relentless barrage of bolts toward Ulfbrand and his followers. Seeing the modron's effectiveness, several Doomguard soldiers form a circle around him, preventing the Ysgardians from neutralizing him. */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushnordomLoc4","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @480 /*Nordom towers over the entire battlefield. Far from sharp swords and axes, out of range of arrows and energy projectiles, he rains death upon Ulfbrand's followers. This is by far the most effective position for him. */
==g-bbd189 IF~Global("G-AmbushgraceLoc4","GLOBAL",3)~THEN @481 /*Far from danger, Fall-from-Grace can use her most powerful healing spells. You see the soldiers' limbs regrow and the fallen return to life. A stream of fresh, strong Doomguard combatants floods the battlefield anew. */
